<!doctype html public "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN//2.0">
<html><head>
<title>Forms home page</title>
</head><body bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#c40026" vlink="#e40026">
<set entity name=title>Form creation page</set>
<read interform file="heading.inc" process>
<read process quiet interform file=tagset.inc>
<tagset-load name=Form-agent-actors>

<hr>
<if-in-group group=admin reporterrors=true>
 <if><get form name=formtype> <then>
 
 <set name=formtype><get form name=formtype></set>
 <write interform file=&formtype;/&formtype;.form>
<h2>&formtype; form</h2>
This is a default template for forms.
Variable to be filled out should be specified with form-variable tags as
below:
 <table>
<TR><TH>Employee<TH>Simple Value to be entered<TH>List of values to choose</TH></TR>
<TR><TD> <form-variable name=employee options=users> </form-variable>
    <TD> <form-variable name=simplevalue> </form-variable>
    <TD> <form-variable name=choicevalue options="choice1 choice2">
         </form-variable>
</TR>
 </table>
Sums and other combinations of variables can also be added, see other forms
for examples.
 </write>
&formtype; has been created, please <a href="edit_form.if?form=&formtype;">
edit</a> this form.  (To add to the list of forms currently requires
re-initialization of the forms server, see the <a href="admin.if">admin</a>
page. 
</then> <else>
<form action="&url;" method=post process copy>

New Form name:<input name="formtype" size="20">
<input type="SUBMIT" value="CreateForm">
</form>
</else></if>

</if-in-group>


